 (expected copied report)‚Üê{replace}CopyLicenseFiles parms;list;path;pkg;name;filename
‚çù (Re)creates a folder Licenses/ and populates it with folders for each Tatin package the project depends on.
‚çù Each such sub-folder contains the corresponding LICENSE file of that package if there is one.
‚çù If there is none then a warning is printed to the session.
‚çù Returns a three-item vector:
‚çù 1. The number of LICENSE files expected
‚çù 2. The number of files copied
‚çù 3. Names of the packages that did not have a LICENSE file\\
‚çù Needs a namespace with two variables: "from" and "to".
‚çù You can prevent the "to"-folder from being re-created by passing a 0 as optional left argument.
‚çù That means that licenses are added to the folder.
 expected‚Üêcopied‚Üê0
 report‚Üê''
 replace‚Üê{0<‚éïNC ‚çµ:‚çé‚çµ ‚ãÑ 1}'replace'
 'Parameter is missing'Assert 2=+/0<parms.‚éïNC‚Üë'from' 'to'
 '"from" is not a directory'Assert ##.FilesAndDirs.IsDir parms.from
 :If 0<‚â¢list‚Üê##.FilesAndDirs.ListDirs2 parms.from,'/'
     path‚Üêparms.to,'/Licenses'
     :If replace
         {}##.FilesAndDirs.RmDirByForce path
     :EndIf
     Assert ##.FilesAndDirs.MkDir path
     :For pkg :In list
         expected+‚Üê1
         name‚Üê‚äÉ{‚ç∫,'-',‚çµ}/2‚Üë'-'(‚â†‚äÜ‚ä¢)‚äÉ,/1‚Üì‚éïNPARTS pkg
         filename‚Üêpkg,'/LICENSE'
         :If ##.FilesAndDirs.IsFile filename
             Assert ##.FilesAndDirs.MkDir path,'/',name
             (path,'/',name)‚éïNCOPY filename
             copied+‚Üê1
         :Else
             report,‚Üê‚äÇname
         :EndIf
     :EndFor
 :EndIf
